column.remarks: The status of the simulation test. Can be idle, rest, charge, discharge, problem, or other.

column.remarks: The cell used in the simulation test. References the cell_type_id in the cells_meta table.

table.name: test_data
table.remarks: Stores test data for tests performed on single cells.

column.name: test_data_id
column.remarks: Unique identifier for the test data point. Auto-incremented upon insertion.

column.name: test_id
column.remarks: The specific test the data point is associated with. References the test_id in the test_meta table.

column.name: cycle
column.remarks: The cycle number of the data point. Tracks number of charge/discharge cycles.

column.name: step
column.remarks: Schedule step associated with the data point.

column.name: test_time_s
column.remarks: The time in seconds since the start of the test, ignoring pauses.

column.name: step_time_s
column.remarks: The time in seconds since the start of the step, ignoring pauses.

column.name: current_ma
column.remarks: The current sourced (or sunk) by the cycler at the specific sample time. Positive for charge, negative for discharge.

column.name: voltage_mv
column.remarks: The voltage measured by the cycler at the specific sample time.

column.name: recorded_datetime
column.remarks: The date and time the data point was recorded by cycler. Matches timezone of cycler.

column.name: unixtime_s
column.remarks: The time in seconds since the Unix epoch (January 1, 1970). Calculated from recorded_datetime.

column.name: thermocouple_temps_c
column.remarks: The temperature (in Celsius) of each thermocouple. Usually T1 is chamber temperature and T2 is cell temperature.

column.name: other_details
column.remarks: Contains data for auxillary measurements.

table.name: test_data_cycle_stats
table.remarks: Stores summary statistics for each cycle for tests performed on single cells.

column.name: cycle_stats_id
column.remarks: Unique identifier for the test data cycle stats. Auto-incremented upon insertion.

column.name: test_id
column.remarks: The specific test the data point is associated with. References the test_id in the test_meta table.

column.name: cycle
column.remarks: The cycle number of the data point. Tracks number of charge/discharge cycles.

column.name: test_time_s
column.remarks: The time in seconds since the start of the test, ignoring pauses.

column.name: reported_charge_capacity_mah
column.remarks: The charge capacity reported by the cycler at the end of the cycle.

column.name: reported_discharge_capacity_mah
column.remarks: The discharge capacity reported by the cycler at the end of the cycle.

column.name: reported_charge_energy_mwh
column.remarks: The charge energy reported by the cycler at the end of the cycle.

column.name: reported_discharge_energy_mwh
column.remarks: The discharge energy reported by the cycler at the end of the cycle.

column.name: calculated_charge_capacity_mah
column.remarks: The charge capacity at the end of the cycle. Calculated from test_data Table values by battetl. Should be the same as reported_charge_capacity_mah.

column.name: calculated_max_charge_temp_c
column.remarks: The maximum temperature during the charge step of the cycle. Calculated from test_data table values by battetl.

column.name: calculated_discharge_capacity_mah
column.remarks: The discharge capacity at the end of the cycle. Calculated from test_data table values by battetl. Should be the same as reported_discharge_capacity_mah.

column.name: calculated_max_discharge_temp_c
column.remarks: The maximum temperature during the discharge step of the cycle. Calculated from test_data table values by battetl.

column.name: calculated_cc_charge_time_s
column.remarks: The time in seconds spent in the constant current charge step of the cycle. Calculated from test_data table values by battetl.

column.name: calculated_cv_charge_time_s
column.remarks: The time in seconds spent in the constant voltage charge step of the cycle. Calculated from test_data table values by battetl.

column.name: calculated_cc_capacity_mah
column.remarks: The capacity in mAh delivered during the constant current charge step of the cycle. Calculated from test_data table values by battetl.

column.name: calculated_cv_capacity_mah
column.remarks: The capacity in mAh delivered during the constant voltage charge step of the cycle. Calculated from test_data table values by battetl.

column.name: calculated_coulombic_efficiency
column.remarks: Ratio of discharge capacity to charge capacity for cycle. Calculated from test_data table values by battetl.

column.name: reported_coulombic_efficiency
column.remarks: Ratio of discharge capacity to charge capacity for cycle. Reported by cycler.

column.name: reported_charge_time_s
column.remarks: The time in seconds spent in the charge step of the cycle. Reported by cycler.

column.name: reported_discharge_time_s
column.remarks: The time in seconds spent in the discharge step of the cycle. Reported by cycler.

column.name: calculated_fifty_percent_charge_time_s
column.remarks: The time in seconds to reach 50% of the final charge capacity for cycle. Calculated from test_data table values by battetl.

column.name: calculated_eighty_percent_charge_time_s
column.remarks: The time in seconds to reach 80% of the final charge capacity for cycle. Calculated from test_data table values by battetl.

column.name: calculated_charge_energy_mwh
column.remarks: The charge energy at the end of the cycle. Calculated from test_data table values by battetl. Should be the same as reported_charge_energy_mwh.

column.name: calculated_discharge_energy_mwh
column.remarks: The discharge energy at the end of the cycle. Calculated from test_data table values by battetl. Should be the same as reported_discharge_energy_mwh.

column.name: other_details
column.remarks: Other details about the test data cycle stats. Contains data for auxillary measurements.

table.remarks: Contains high-level information about tests on single cells.

column.name: test_id
column.remarks: Unique identifier for the test. Auto-incremented upon insertion.

column.name: cell_id
column.remarks: Specific cell being tested. References the cell_id in the cells table.

column.name: schedule_id
column.remarks: Schedule file used in the test. References the schedule_id in the schedule_meta table.

column.name: test_name
column.remarks: Name of the test in cycling software.

column.name: start_date
column.remarks: Date the test was started. Populated manually in config file.

column.name: end_date
column.remarks: Date the test was ended. Populated manually in config file.

column.name: channel
column.remarks: Cycler channel the test was run on.

column.name: ev_chamber
column.remarks: The environmental chamber the test was run in.

column.name: ev_chamber_slot
column.remarks: The slot in the environmental chamber the test was run in.

column.name: thermocouples
column.remarks: Specific thermocouple attached to the cell being tested.

column.name: thermocouple_channels
column.remarks: Channel the thermocouple is attached to.

column.name: comments
column.remarks: Additional info about the test.

column.name: project_id
column.remarks: Project the test is associated with. References the project_id in the projects table.

column.name: test_capacity_mah
column.remarks: Rated capacity of the cell being tested.

column.name: potentiostat_id
column.remarks: Potentiostat the test was run on. References the potentiostat_id in the potentiostats table.

column.name: cycler_id
column.remarks: Cycler the test was run on. References the cycler_id in the cyclers table.
